node.title: Body pulled from Sunshine Coast surf after divers search for missing man
node.alt: An empty wooden table soaked by rain and illuminated next to the darkness of the sea at night
node.description: A body is found in waters off Shelley Beach near Caloundra, almost 24 hours after a Brisbane man went missing along a treacherous stretch of beach.
node.content: ["The body of a man has been found\u00a0in waters off Shelley Beach near Caloundra,\u00a0almost 24 hours\u00a0after a\u00a0man went missing along a treacherous stretch of beach.", "Water Police on jet skis found the man in waters south of where he went missing, Queensland police said in a statement.", "Surf Lifesaving crews have been at the scene\u00a0since before dawn, dispatching two rescue vessels, and\u00a0a surveillance drone in the hopes of finding Ferny Hills man Travis Davis.", "The Westpac Rescue helicopter has also provided aerial support through the morning.", "The conditions are worsening, with high winds forcing rescuers to withdraw the drone.", "Travis Davis and a second person were swimming at Shelley Beach in the late afternoon on Saturday when passers-by on the beach saw them begin to struggle.", "Three people entered the water to help the pair, but only one of the swimmers was pulled to safety.", "The second man, also in his 20s, remains in hospital.", "More to come."]
